# Frontend Patterns

## Structure
- Pages in `frontend/src/pages/` (Login, Register, Dashboard, Orders, Users)
- Components in `frontend/src/components/` (e.g. ProtectedRoute)
- Auth in `frontend/src/contexts/AuthContext.jsx`
- API client in `frontend/src/services/api.js`

## Auth Flow
- JWT stored in localStorage after login
- Axios interceptor adds `Authorization: Bearer <token>` to requests
- ProtectedRoute wraps pages requiring auth
- Superusers see "Users" menu; regular users do not

## API Client
- Base URL: `/api` (proxied in dev)
- Use Axios from `frontend/src/services/api.js` (includes auth interceptor)
- Handle 401 → redirect to login; 403 → show error

## UI Conventions
- Use modal dialogs for error messages (per FUNCTIONS_SPECS)
- Loading spinners during API calls
- Denormalize order data: one table row per line item when displaying orders
- Orders page supports grouped-by-order mode; selection should persist across grouped/product view toggles
- Keep bulk-action options view-aware: product actions in product view, order actions in grouped view
- Combined processing flow ("Preuzmite za obradu") uses three fixed payment combinations and refresh-after-action should preserve that scope
